messages.content: What is the purpose of the ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension?
The ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension introduces logic nodes and conditional rendering capabilities to ComfyUI.
What are some of the nodes included in the ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension?
The ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension includes nodes such as If, Compare, Int, String, Float, Bool, If ANY return A else B, and DebugPrint.
How can the ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension be installed?

The ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension can be installed by cloning the repository into the 'custom_nodes' folder of ComfyUI, using ComfyUI Manager, or using the comfy registry command 'comfy node registry-install comfyui-logic'.
What operators are supported by the Compare node in ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension?
The Compare node in ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension supports operators such as 'a == b', 'a != b', 'a < b', 'a > b', 'a <= b', and 'a >= b'.
What does the If ANY return A else B node do in ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension?
The If ANY return A else B node in ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension passes the value of the IF_TRUE node if the ANY input is True, otherwise it passes the IF_FALSE node.
What is the purpose of the DebugPrint node in ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension?
The DebugPrint node in ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension prints the provided input to the console, which is useful for debugging.
Who is the author of the ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension?
The author of the ComfyUI Logic Nodes Extension is David Fischer, who goes by the GitHub username 'theUpsider'.
What is the purpose of the Bug Report in ComfyUI-Logic?
The Bug Report in ComfyUI-Logic is used to create a report that helps improve the system by identifying and describing bugs.
What should be included in the description of the bug?
The description of the bug should be clear and concise, explaining what the bug is.
What is required to make it easier for others to reproduce the error?
To make it easier for others to reproduce the error, please attach a workflow file.
What should be described in the 'Expected behavior' section?
In the 'Expected behavior' section, a clear and concise description of what you expected to happen should be provided.
Are screenshots necessary when reporting a bug?
Screenshots are not always necessary, but they can be added to help explain the problem if applicable.
What version information should be included in the bug report?
The ComfyUI Version should be included in the bug report.
What can be added in the 'Additional context' section of the bug report?
Any other context about the problem can be added in the 'Additional context' section of the bug report.
What is the purpose of the Feature request template in ComfyUI-Logic?

The Feature request template in ComfyUI-Logic is used to suggest an idea for the project by providing a clear and concise description of the problem, the desired solution, alternative solutions considered, and any additional context or screenshots.
What should be included in the 'Is your feature request related to a problem?' section of the Feature request template?
In the 'Is your feature request related to a problem?' section, you should provide a clear and concise description of the problem you are facing, for example, 'I'm always frustrated when [...]'.
What information should be provided in the 'Describe the solution you'd like' section of the Feature request template?
In the 'Describe the solution you'd like' section, you should give a clear and concise description of what you want to happen or how you envision the feature working in ComfyUI-Logic.
What should be included in the 'Describe alternatives you've considered' section of the Feature request template?
In the 'Describe alternatives you've considered' section, provide a clear and concise description of any alternative solutions or features you've considered before making the feature request.
What can be added in the 'Additional context' section of the Feature request template?
In the 'Additional context' section, you can add any other relevant information, context, or screenshots that can help explain or support your feature request for ComfyUI-Logic.
Is it necessary to assign labels when submitting a Feature request using the template in ComfyUI-Logic?
No, it is not necessary to assign labels when submitting a Feature request using the template, as the labels field is left blank in the provided template.
Should assignees be specified when submitting a Feature request using the template in ComfyUI-Logic?
No, it is not required to specify assignees when submitting a Feature request using the template, as the assignees field is left blank in the provided template.
